column5:
Kill grade E, spread out C and D to cover that space

Note that this will require a database update:

UPDATE scans SET grade = 'C' WHERE score < 60 AND score >= 50;
UPDATE scans SET grade = 'C-' WHERE score < 50 AND score >= 45;
UPDATE scans SET grade = 'D+' WHERE score < 45 AND score >= 40;
UPDATE scans SET grade = 'D' WHERE score < 40 AND score >= 30;
UPDATE scans SET grade = 'D-' WHERE score < 30 AND score >= 25;
REFRESH MATERIALIZED VIEW grade_distribution;
